   {:e #blake3 "0d17373b492161281c5d4a7defcfcb1dda52d56e46b3f544d4778a5a30bbc3c3" :a :task/description :v "BACKGROUND: Not every team wants an interactive conversation. Some know exactly what they need. Pre-built manifests for common domains let teams start immediately. Each manifest is a .edn file containing policy datoms.. APPROACH: (1) Create manifests/ directory in repo. (2) ddis.edn: current DDIS policy (7 boundaries, INV/ADR/NEG claim types, witness evidence, harvest urgency). (3) research.edn: scientific research policy (hypothesis/theory/conjecture claims, experiment/replication/meta-analysis evidence, hypothesis-experiment and theory-prediction boundaries). (4) compliance.edn: regulatory compliance policy (requirement/control/exception claims, audit-finding/test-of-controls evidence, requirement-control and control-evidence boundaries, control-gap anomaly). (5) agile.edn: agile product development (user-story/acceptance-criteria claims, test-result/review evidence, story-test boundary). (6) Each manifest includes comments explaining the domain mapping. (7) braid init --manifest manifests/research.edn loads the file and transacts.. ACCEPTANCE: (A) 4 manifest files exist and parse correctly. (B) Each produces valid policy (passes validate_policy). (C) F(S) is meaningful for each domain (not vacuously 1.0). (D) braid init --manifest <file> works for all 4. (E) Each manifest has inline documentation explaining the domain mapping. DEPENDS-ON: POLICY-1 (t-f5298b23), POLICY-5 (t-c2bb5b31). FILE: manifests/ddis.edn, manifests/research.edn, manifests/compliance.edn, manifests/agile.edn" :op :assert}
